<TITLE> Mother and son die in road accident </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Bogra, June 7 (bdnews24.com)  A mother and son died when their car lost control and fell into a road-side ditch. The accident took place at the Bagura-Naoga highway's Pota area of Adamdighi upazila at 1am on Sunday night. The dead were identified as Rahicha Beoa, 65, and her son Abdur Raub,45, residents of Naoga sadar upazila's Shahjadpur village. Adamdighi officer in charge Mohammad Mozammel Haque told bdnews24.com that after attending a family program at Dhaka, the two had started out in a private car set for Naoga The car however lost control on a bridge at Pota rail-crossing of Adamdighi and fell into a nearby road-side ditch, he added. "They died on the spot and the car-driver fled the place immediately," the officer in charge said. On Monday morning, the two bodies were delivered to their family. bdn
